outline:
1. entrance, a coming in, entering
  2. sunset
    1. sunset
    2. sunset, west
kjv_def: by which came, as cometh, in coming, as men enter into, entering, entrance into, entry, where goeth, going down, [phrase] westward. Compare H4126 (מוֹבָא).
strongs_def: an entrance (the place or the act); specifically sunset or the west; also (adverb with preposition) towards
